The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Mayor Sovan Chatterjee resigned from the advisory committee of the Garden Reach waterworks on Wednesday, following a report from the civic water supply department that the Calcutta Metropolitan Water and Sanitation Authority had ignored the panels advice.  he authority, a state government body, runs the waterworks. Large parts of south Calcutta often go without water following snags in the utility.   Metro Railway: The railway ministry has sanctioned Rs 15 crore for the development of Metro Railway stations and Rs 1,000 crore for the upgrade of infrastructure, Mamata Banerjee said on Wednesday. The railway minister also declared the Metro Railway as the 17th zone of the Indian Railways.  Suicides: Kishor Mitra, a resident of Jadavpur, was found hanging in his room late on Tuesday. The same night Class XI student Iti Mondal was found hanging in her Barasat home. On Wednesday afternoon, Rupali Ghosh, 27, was found hanging in her in-laws house in Jagaddal. Rupalis husband and in-laws have been detained.   Sentenced: Manjit Singh alias Mange, facing a murder trial, was sentenced to one years rigorous imprisonment on Wednesday for escaping from custody. Mange and his associates, wanted in a murder case in Uttar Pradesh, were arrested on Park Street in 1998 by a team of Uttar Pradesh police. He had escaped from judicial custody while undergoing treatment at SSKM Hospital in 1998.                                                                                                                                               
